---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-[rgb(8,25,25)]">
    <Header />

    <main class="container mx-auto px-4 pt-28 pb-16 max-w-3xl text-white">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#02f1dc] mb-6">
        Purro Wallet Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#b1cac4] mb-8">
        Effective date: 11/08/2025 · Contact: hello@purro.xyz · Website:
        <a
          class="underline hover:text-white"
          href="https://purro.xyz/privacy"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">https://purro.xyz/privacy</a
        >
      </p>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Overview</h2>
        <p>
          Purro is a non-custodial Web3 wallet. We do not collect, sell, or
          share your personal information for advertising. Your seed phrase and
          private keys are encrypted and stored locally on your device and never
          leave it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Data We Process</h2>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">
          Local wallet data (stored on your device):
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Encrypted seed phrase, private keys, and password</li>
          <li>
            Wallet addresses, labels, settings, token/NFT caches, and UI
            preferences
          </li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Blockchain data:</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>
            Public on-chain information such as wallet addresses, balances, and
            transactions
          </li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">
          Service interaction data (when you use features):
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>
            Requests to blockchain/RPC and market data providers (may include
            your IP address and wallet address necessary to fulfill the request)
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">How We Use Data</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>
            Provide wallet functionality: connect to dApps, sign
            messages/transactions, show balances/portfolio
          </li>
          <li>
            Operate features reliably: refresh data, auto-lock, and background
            tasks compliant with Chrome MV3
          </li>
          <li>Notify you of transaction/signing status (if enabled)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Legal bases (where applicable, e.g., GDPR): performance of a contract,
          legitimate interests in operating the service, and/or your consent
          (e.g., notifications).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          When you use wallet features, requests may be sent to third-party
          services to read or broadcast data, for example:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>
            RPC/node providers (e.g., Alchemy) for reading/pushing transactions
          </li>
          <li>
            Indexers/market data (e.g., GeckoTerminal) for pricing/metadata
          </li>
          <li>
            Protocol-specific APIs (e.g., Hyperliquid, Hyperscan) for related
            features
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These providers may process your IP address and wallet address to
          deliver results. Please review their privacy policies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Storage &amp; Security</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>
            Sensitive data (seed/keys) is encrypted and stored locally on your
            device
          </li>
          <li>We do not upload seed/keys to our servers</li>
          <li>
            You are responsible for safeguarding your device, seed phrase, and
            password
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Your Choices &amp; Rights</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>
            Export, reset, or delete local wallet data and caches in settings at
            any time
          </li>
          <li>
            Withdraw consent for optional features (e.g., disable notifications)
          </li>
          <li>
            If local laws grant additional rights (GDPR/CCPA), contact us at
            [support@email.com].
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>Note: We cannot recover your seed/keys as we never store them.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Data Retention</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>
            Wallet data remains on your device until you reset or uninstall the
            extension
          </li>
          <li>
            Minimal technical logs (if any) are retained only as necessary and
            purged on a reasonable schedule
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">International Transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Requests to third-party providers may be processed on servers outside
          your country. Their policies and safeguards apply to those transfers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Children’s Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The wallet is not directed to individuals under 18. We do not
          knowingly collect data from children.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Cookies &amp; Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          No advertising trackers. We use browser storage and local caching
          strictly to operate wallet features.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Browser Permissions &amp; APIs</h2>
        <p>
          We use browser permissions (e.g., storage, scripting, notifications,
          side panel, alarms, offscreen) solely to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Store local wallet data/settings</li>
          <li>Inject a standard provider for dApp connectivity</li>
          <li>Present signing/transaction UI and refresh data</li>
          <li>
            Schedule auto-lock/cache maintenance and run compliant background
            tasks
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not execute remotely hosted code.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mb-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy. Changes will be posted at
          <a
            class="underline hover:text-white"
            href="https://purro.xyz/privacy"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener">https://purro.xyz/privacy</a
          >
          with an updated “Effective date.”
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Contact Us</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-1">
          <li>Data controller: Terran Thai</li>
          <li>Email: terrancrypt@gmail.com</li>
          <li>Address: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[#b1cac4]">
          Notes: Blockchain data is public and cannot be altered or erased.
          Share your wallet address and sign transactions only with trusted
          parties.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>
